newsitem.title: USA: CBOT soybeans seen 3-5 cents higher on crush data.
newsitem.headline: CBOT soybeans seen 3-5 cents higher on crush data.

text.p: CBOT soybean futures were expected to open three to five cents per bushel higher Friday on a higher-than-expected crushing pace, traders said.
"When I saw the crush last night, I knew we'd be at least three to five cents higher," said a commission house trader.
Thursday afternoon, National Oilseed Processors Association reported a weekly crushing pace of 25.632 million bushels.
That figure exceeded trade expectations for a crush of 24.0 to 25.45 million bushels.
Other supportive factors in Friday's trade include rainy forecasts for soaked areas of the eastern Corn Belt, rumors of Chinese buying interest and technical strength, traders said.
